The paper deals with dimension reduction and statistical methods for data analysis, which are common topics in machine learning and computer vision (cs.LG and cs.CV). The problem of compressive robust subspace clustering involves matrix operations and optimization, which are also relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the proposed method involves computational efficiency, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
